Git is a version control system. If any changes are made to the code it will be saved as new version. with the help of version control you can easyly go back to the old version. reverting to old version is so simple.
You can see who has made what changes to the code from Git.
Note: Version should be enabled in Git.
Git - it is used on local system.
Github- its used at cloud level to save code at a centralized location and to push the deployment via pipelines.

Example:

Develop a clock. Which language will you use.

We use Python.
Why phython?
It has large number built in libraries available. you can call the library and use it.

keyword to call the library? 
Ans: import

Interview question:

What is the command to go back to previous version in Git?
Ans: Git revert

Note: This is possible only if you are maintaing the version.

What is Artifacts?
Compail the code and a binary file will be created and with the help of binary file merge with the packages and build will be ready. This is called Build or Artifact.

Note: Build or Artifact is the same. But use Artifacts in interview for better package.

What is README file? Interview question.
You can see information about the repository, project, code and instructions how to use it. How to run it. how to create it.how to delete it.

